    "## Ethics\n",
    "\n",
    "### A. Data Collection\n",
    "- [X] **A.1 Informed consent**  \n",
    "This project uses publicly available datasets (IMDb via Kaggle), so no human subjects are directly involved and informed consent is not required.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **A.2 Collection bias**  \n",
    "Both datasets are biased toward popular, Western, and high-budget films, which may underrepresent non-US industries such as Bollywood, Nollywood, or Korean cinema. This directly affects our US vs. non-US comparison. We explicitly report sample sizes by country group and acknowledge this imbalance when interpreting results.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **A.3 Limit PII exposure**  \n",
    "The datasets do not include personally identifiable information. All data points represent films, not individuals, so privacy risks are minimal.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **A.4 Downstream bias mitigation**  \n",
    "Because our datasets skew toward Hollywood productions, conclusions drawn from non-US subgroups may be less statistically reliable. We flag this limitation in our results and avoid overgeneralizing from underrepresented groups. Where possible, we use proportional sampling or sensitivity analyses to check robustness.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### B. Data Storage\n",
    "- [X] **B.1 Data security**  \n",
    "Data is stored in a private GitHub repository and on local machines accessible only to team members.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **B.2 Right to be forgotten**  \n",
    "All data used is publicly available and contains no personal information, so the right to be forgotten is not directly applicable. If personally identifiable data were inadvertently included, it would be removed immediately.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **B.3 Data retention plan**  \n",
    "Data will only be used for the duration of this academic project. All local copies will be deleted upon course completion and the repository archived.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### C. Analysis\n",
    "- [X] **C.1 Missing perspectives**  \n",
    "Our datasets significantly underrepresent non-English-language and non-Western film industries. Findings from non-US subgroups will be interpreted cautiously with sample sizes reported.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **C.2 Dataset bias**  \n",
    "We examine potential bias in genre representation and budget reporting, including checking whether certain genres or countries are systematically underrepresented in ways that could distort comparisons.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **C.3 Honest representation**  \n",
    "All visualizations and conclusions accurately reflect the underlying data. We will not cherry-pick results and will report null or unexpected findings alongside positive ones.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **C.4 Privacy in analysis**  \n",
    "No personal data will be displayed or used. Analysis operates at the film level, not the individual level.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **C.5 Auditability**  \n",
    "All analysis is documented in reproducible Jupyter notebooks, version-controlled on GitHub.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### D. Modeling\n",
    "- [X] **D.1 Proxy discrimination**  \n",
    "Country of production and original language are used as structural variables, not as proxies for race or ethnicity. We will not frame results in ways that imply value judgments about different film industries or cultures.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **D.2 Fairness across groups**  \n",
    "We report results separately for US vs. non-US films and for pre/post-2015 periods, so patterns specific to smaller groups are not masked. We report confidence intervals and note where group sizes are too small for reliable inference.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **D.3 Metric selection**  \n",
    "We acknowledge that box office revenue does not capture streaming income or home video sales, and that IMDb ratings may reflect demographic biases in the IMDb user base rather than true global audience opinion.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **D.4 Explainability**  \n",
    "Methods and results will be clearly explained in plain language alongside technical details, with visualizations to aid accessibility.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **D.5 Communicate limitations**  \n",
    "We explicitly state dataset limitations, potential sources of bias, and boundaries on generalizability in both our notebooks and final report.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### E. Deployment\n",
    "- [X] **E.1 Monitoring and evaluation**  \n",
    "This is an academic project with no ongoing deployment. We document all analytical decisions so any future use can be evaluated against original design choices.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **E.2 Redress**  \n",
    "If errors are identified, we will revise our analysis, correct affected conclusions, and clearly document what changed and why.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **E.3 Roll back**  \n",
    "All analysis is version-controlled on GitHub, allowing rollback to any prior version if a change introduces errors.\n",
    "\n",
    "- [X] **E.4 Unintended use**  \n",
    "We will consider how results could be misinterpreted — for example, as suggesting non-US films are inferior — and communicate findings responsibly with appropriate context and caveats.\n"
